tspan.tspan: What is Ye Old Gamer's Gathering?
Meeting once a week after school, Ye Olde
Gamer’s Gathering is the official RSS games
club. This is a free, friendly and fun way to
immerse yourself into awesome games. Our
club is open to all students and any type of
board game, role playing game or trading
card game. Join us and get your adventure
started!
What is a Role Playing Game?
RPG stands for role-playing game. In the
game club we play TTRPG (tabletop role-
playing games) which involve players
interacting “in real life” with each other and
other physical objects, like dice, books, pen,
paper, maps and sometimes small figurines
called “miniatures”. RPGs cover every sort of
genre, and vary from sci-fi to fantasy, take
place right here on Earth or are set in distant
worlds and far off places. There are RPGs
that are based on Avatar the Last Airbender
and even Jumanji! You play the role of a
character and immerse yourself into their
journey with the help and guidance of a
master storyteller who keeps the game and
the players working towards a common goal
or achievement. So if you are looking for a
fun escape from everyday blandness, have a
cool idea and want to take players into your
creation, or you want to be a player in
someone else’s story, insert yourself into one
of our many fun RPG sessions!
What types of RPGs do you play?
Although we have typically focused on
playing Dungeons & Dragons, we do not
place any limitations on our members. D&D
is a well known and loved RPG, which is why
most of our members are drawn to it, but if
you are interested in another system, all you
need is to find another member who is
willing to play with you. At game club, we
are all about trying new things and making
new friends, so we say lead on!
What is a Trading Card Game?
TGM stands for trading card game. There are
several well known TGMs, such as Magic the
Gathering (Magic or MTG for short), Keyforge
and Pokemon, just to name a few. Although
most of our members who are into playing
TGMs as their main activity play Magic, we
encourage variety, so if there is another TGM
that interests you, bring it and find a friend to
play with!
What board games do you play?
We play a wide variety of board games, from
the traditional to the unconventional. Each
week there are a variety of new games to
choose from as well as a standard collection
of games owned by the school. If you have a
board game that you love and would like to
share it with us, bring it in and we will play it
together!
Do I have to pick just one type of
game to play?
No way! We encourage our members to try
new things and explore all of our varied
choices. Having choices is what game club
is all about, well that and having fun while
you are here!
Does it cost anything to be a member?
Membership is, and always will be, free. We
do require that you agree to and follow our
Habits of Crew. Games can become
competitive and intense, and we expect every
member to always treat others with respect,
kindness and empathy.
When and where does the club meet?
We meet every Wednesday after school ends
and finish up by 6:30PM. We do occasionally
have to cancel our meeting if we do not have
enough staff in attendance or for other rare
circumstances, such as snow days. If we
have to cancel, we will communicate this to
our members as early as possible. We start
our meetings in the first floor Middle School
Crew Space and break out from there into
other rooms. We also occasionally use the
Commons if it is available. We will let the
club know when our meeting location is
going to change. Because we meet away
from the pick-up area, we require that
parents come to our meeting place to pick up
their student if they need to leave before
6:30PM. For the safety of our members,
we
do not allow anyone to leave early, unless
one of our staff members receives direct
communication from their parents or
guardian.
Welcome Friend!
This guide will give you the
basics about what types
of games we play as well
as when and where we
meet.
